# Foremanctl Migration Project
# Migrating foreman-maintain functionality into foremanctl

## Context
- foreman-maintain: Ruby-based tool (Clamp CLI) for health checks, maintenance, upgrades of Foreman/Katello
- foremanctl: Python/Ansible-based tool (Obsah CLI framework wrapping Ansible playbooks) for containerized Foreman deployment
- Source repos:
  - /home/vagrant/foreman_maintain (foreman-maintain, Ruby)
  - /home/vagrant/foremanctl (foremanctl, Python/Ansible)
- See docs/ for evolving design, migration map, and discoveries

## Architecture Quick Reference
- foremanctl commands = Ansible playbooks in src/playbooks/<name>/<name>.yaml
- foremanctl checks = Ansible roles in src/roles/check_<name>/, registered in src/roles/checks/tasks/main.yml
- foremanctl features = plugin registry in src/features.yaml (NOT same as foreman-maintain features)
- CLI framework = obsah (pip package), auto-discovers playbooks, exposes as subcommands
- CLI params defined in metadata.obsah.yaml per playbook, passed as Ansible extra vars
- Output formatting via custom Ansible callback plugin in src/callback_plugins/foremanctl.py

## Current State (as of 2026-04-21)
- foremanctl has 4 commands: checks, deploy, features, pull-images
- foreman-maintain has 12 commands: health, upgrade, update, service, backup, restore, packages, advanced, plugin, self-upgrade, maintenance-mode, report
- ~53 checks in foreman-maintain, 4-6 check roles in foremanctl
- Migration priority: health checks → service mgmt → maintenance mode → packages → backup/restore → upgrade

